      "description": "Experienced Protagonist: Except for Cameron (who has his own experience in the form of being a military veteran), the team has been working together and fighting Red Flag for months, if not longer, when the pilot begins. Ragtag Bunch of Misfits: The team is made up of aSilver FoxScience Hero, aTeam Momwith aCompelling Voice, aLightning Bruisercop who intially feels that the team is beneath him, a young woman with family issues and powers that cause aSensory Overload, an autisticTechnopath, and a veteran withSuper-ReflexesandImprobable Aiming Skills. Two Girls to a Team: In the first season, Rachel and Nina are the only female members of the team, not counting their handler Sullivan, who isCommuting on a Bus. A neurologist and psychologist who specialises in the study of \"alphas\". He leads the DOD-sponsored team of Alphas, but is slowly becoming disillusioned as the team's mandate shifts from finding and helping Alphas in trouble to fighting dangerous Alphas and locking them up. He started investigating the Alpha phenomenon after discovering that his daughter was one. Ambiguously Jewish: Lee Rosen. He has a common Ashkenazi last name and has fairly Jewish looks.",
      "source": "tvtropes"
